
Steps to configure maven

	Download apache maven -- 3.3.9-bin.zip
	extract this folder
	copy path -- E:\MySofts\apache-maven-3.3.9

	System Env Variables
		MAVEN_HOME=E:\MySofts\apache-maven-3.3.9
		path = --------------------;%MAVEN_HOME%\bin
	
	Open Fresh Command Prompt
	type
		>mvn
	
	C:\users\{login account name}\			.m2\repository
											    \copy here -- settings.xml from git repo - https://github.com/yogymax/seleniumwithSettingsxml/tree/master/src/main/java/com/scp
												
	Eclipse--File -- New -- Other -- Maven Project -- Select Location and then Next or keep as it is -- Maven-archtype-quickstart(DesktopApp) -- You  need to specify
		--group_id -- tells about group name/account name -- this project belongs to 				which grp in a company
		--artifact_id --- Project Name -- what is the project name
		version -- which version you are currently developing
		package -- folder strucutre
		
		
		Click Finish
	
	
	FYI --- Maven_archtype-Webapp(Webapp)
	
	
	HibernateApp
		src/main/java -- always holds business logic
		src/test/java -- testing logic -- unit test cases /whitebox testing /module base/
		src/test/resources -- it holds required resources for testing logic--test data/conf
		src/main/resources ---- it holds required resources for Business logic--test data/conf
		Libraries
			Maven dependencies -- all dependencies which we are going to specify inside 	pom.xml
			JRE Lib -- java lib dependencies
		src -- folder structure view -- dont care abt this
		target -- apke project ka jar will be created here
		pom.xml --- project object model
	
	Why maven
		-- it resolves transitive dependencies automatically
		--Every developer in a projects will get same version of jar -- output consistent
		-- Size k hisaab se compact and can be shared
		
		
	In case any issues in archtype	https://howtodoinjava.com/eclipse/how-to-import-maven-remote-archetype-catalogs-in-eclipse/
	
	
	take hibernate project from repository -- download
		
	
	
	
		
		
